-- England Cricket's James Anderson Cracks Rib, Expected to be Fit for Ashes
-- B y   B o b   B e n s c h
-- 2010-10-15T10:34:38Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-15/england-cricket-s-james-anderson-cracks-rib-expected-to-be-fit-for-ashes.html
England fast-bowler James Anderson
is expected to be fit for the Ashes series in Australia after
cracking a rib in training.  Anderson was injured during a recent preparation camp in
Germany, the England and Wales Cricket Board said on its
website.  The England squad will fly to Australia on Oct. 29 and
Anderson is expected to be available for the first Ashes Test
Nov. 25-29 in Brisbane.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Bob Bensch at 
 bbensch@bloomberg.net  